{"lemma":"صُعُودٌ","slug":"صُعُودٌ","root":"ص.ع.د","root_slug":"ص-ع-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ع-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صُعُودٌ","root":"صعد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24322"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8F%D8%B9%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَعِدَ (ṣaʕida) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"climbing, mounting"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ascension"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of صَعِدَ (ṣaʕida)."},"ipa":["/sˤu.ʕuːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24322","headword_ar":"صَعُودٌ","root":"SEd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An acclivity; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"habuwTN","text_ar":"هَبُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaduwrN","text_ar":"حَدُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEadN","text_ar":"صَعَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [syn. therewith, being]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SababN","text_ar":"صَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEaAy^idu","text_ar":"صَعَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEudN","text_ar":"صُعُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ascending road:"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the fem. gender: pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoEidapN","text_ar":"اَصْعِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEudN","text_ar":"صُعُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mountain-road difficult of ascent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEuwdaA='u","text_ar":"صَعُودَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEadaA='u","text_ar":"صُعَدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kA^d","text_ar":"كاد"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a difficult place of ascent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in that art.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aEuwdu","text_ar":"الصَّعُودُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain mountain in Hell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, MF,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of fire, which the unbeliever will ascend during a period of seventy years, after which he will fall down it, and thus he will do for ever:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is of one live coal; the unbeliever will be compelled to ascend it, and will be beaten with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqaAmiE","text_ar":"مَقَامِع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqomaEapN","text_ar":"مِقْمَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and whenever he puts his leg upon it, it will dissolve as high as the lower part of his hip, and will then become replaced whole and sound."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-  [Hence also,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Difficulty, grievousness, distress, affliction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trouble;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEadN","text_ar":"صَعَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEodaA='u","text_ar":"صَعْدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEadaA='u","text_ar":"صُعَدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEodudN","text_ar":"صُعْدُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohaqotuhu SaEuwdFA","text_ar":"اَرْهَقْتُهُ صَعُودًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constrained him, to do a difficult, grievous, distressing, afflicting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"troublesome, thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I imposed upon him such a punishment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lils~iyaAdapi SaEodaA='u","text_ar":"لِلسِّيَادَةِ صَعْدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEadaA='u","text_ar":"صُعَدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"? (see above)] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is a difficult,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressing, ascent to lordship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mastery."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamapN","text_ar":"اَكَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu SuEadaA='a","text_ar":"ذَاتُ صُعَدَا=ءَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hill difficult to ascend."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b3-  Also A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that brings forth a young one imperfectly formed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after six or seven months,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is made to take an affection to the young one of the preceding year,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and takes an affection to the young one of the preceding year:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose young one dies, and which returns to her former young one, and yields it milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"when she does this, her milk is the sweeter: (Lth:) or a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that brings forth her young one after its hair has grown, and then takes an affection to her former young one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the young one of another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEaAy^idu","text_ar":"صَعَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEudN","text_ar":"صُعُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this latter pl. is disapproved by Sb. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","MF","A","As","Lth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}